# Architecture document — read and maintain

[`ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) is the canonical map of Backoffice.

## Before starting work

1. **Read** `ARCHITECTURE.md` and [`docs/domain-specification.md`](../../docs/domain-specification.md).
2. Skim sibling components/services for patterns.
3. For template/UI work, read [`docs/ui/README.md`](../../docs/ui/README.md) ([backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc](backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc)).

## Before marking a task done

Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` when routes, services, proxies, or roles change.  
Update `docs/domain-specification.md` for new UI labels or shell concepts ([domain-model.mdc](domain-model.mdc)).  
Update `docs/ui/` when UI patterns or screens change ([backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc](backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc)).

## Never

- Add routes or services without checking ARCHITECTURE.md.
- Leave docs stale after structural changes.
